   "source": [
    "{\n",
    " \"cells\": [\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m001\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# Credit Default Exploratory Analysis\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Project Overview\\n\",\n",
    "    \"This notebook analyzes borrower and repayment data to identify patterns associated with default risk. We focus on distributions, correlations, and interpretable risk drivers.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Learning Objectives\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Explore borrower characteristics and their relationship to default.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Identify the strongest risk factors using EDA techniques.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Visualize default patterns across borrower segments.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Discuss implications for credit risk management.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Business / Research Problem\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Lenders need to assess default risk before extending credit. Understanding which borrower features predict default helps build better scoring models.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Why This Analysis Matters\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Even a 1% improvement in default prediction can save millions in losses for a lending portfolio.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m002\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Dataset Overview\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Synthetic dataset of **5,000 loan records** with borrower attributes and default status.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Dataset Source and License Notes\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Synthetically generated for educational purposes.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c001\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"import subprocess, sys, importlib\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for pkg in [\\\"pandas\\\", \\\"numpy\\\", \\\"matplotlib\\\", \\\"seaborn\\\", \\\"scipy\\\"]:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    try:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        importlib.import_module(pkg)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    except ImportError:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        subprocess.check_call([sys.executable, \\\"-m\\\", \\\"pip\\\", \\\"install\\\", \\\"-q\\\", pkg])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"Environment ready.\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c002\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"import numpy as np\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import pandas as pd\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import seaborn as sns\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from scipy import stats\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import warnings\\n\",\n",
    "    \"warnings.filterwarnings(\\\"ignore\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"sns.set_style(\\\"whitegrid\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"%matplotlib inline\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c003\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"SEED = 42\\n\",\n",
    "    \"N = 5000\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"Configuration loaded.\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c004\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"rng = np.random.default_rng(SEED)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"rows = []\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for i in range(N):\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    age = int(rng.normal(38, 10))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    age = np.clip(age, 21, 70)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    income = max(15000, int(rng.normal(55000, 20000)))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    loan_amount = max(1000, int(rng.normal(15000, 8000)))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    credit_score = int(np.clip(rng.normal(680, 60), 300, 850))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    dti_ratio = np.clip(rng.normal(0.35, 0.12), 0.05, 0.80)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    employment_years = max(0, int(rng.exponential(5)))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    has_mortgage = int(rng.random() < 0.45)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    loan_purpose = rng.choice([\\\"Debt Consolidation\\\", \\\"Home Improvement\\\", \\\"Medical\\\", \\\"Education\\\", \\\"Auto\\\"])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\n\",\n",
    "    \"    # Default probability based on features\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    default_prob = 0.08\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    default_prob += (700 - credit_score) * 0.0005\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    default_prob += (dti_ratio - 0.35) * 0.3\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    default_prob -= employment_years * 0.005\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    default_prob += (loan_amount / income) * 0.05\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    default_prob = np.clip(default_prob + rng.normal(0, 0.03), 0.01, 0.60)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    defaulted = int(rng.random() < default_prob)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\n\",\n",
    "    \"    rows.append({\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"loan_id\\\": f\\\"L{i+1:05d}\\\", \\\"age\\\": age, \\\"income\\\": income,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"loan_amount\\\": loan_amount, \\\"credit_score\\\": credit_score,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"dti_ratio\\\": round(dti_ratio, 3), \\\"employment_years\\\": employment_years,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"has_mortgage\\\": has_mortgage, \\\"loan_purpose\\\": loan_purpose,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"defaulted\\\": defaulted,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    })\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df = pd.DataFrame(rows)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Dataset: {df.shape}, Default rate: {df['defaulted'].mean():.1%}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df.head()\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c005\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Missing: {df.isnull().sum().sum()}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"✅ Validation passed.\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c006\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 3, figsize=(16, 10))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for ax, col in zip(axes.flat, [\\\"credit_score\\\", \\\"income\\\", \\\"loan_amount\\\", \\\"dti_ratio\\\", \\\"age\\\", \\\"employment_years\\\"]):\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    for label, color in [(0, \\\"#2ecc71\\\"), (1, \\\"#e74c3c\\\")]:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        subset = df[df[\\\"defaulted\\\"] == label]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        ax.hist(subset[col], bins=30, alpha=0.5, label=\\\"Default\\\" if label else \\\"No Default\\\", color=color)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    ax.set_title(col)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    ax.legend()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.tight_layout()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.show()\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c007\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# Default rate by credit score bands\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df[\\\"credit_band\\\"] = pd.cut(df[\\\"credit_score\\\"], bins=[300,580,660,720,780,850], labels=[\\\"Poor\\\",\\\"Fair\\\",\\\"Good\\\",\\\"Very Good\\\",\\\"Excellent\\\"])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"band_default = df.groupby(\\\"credit_band\\\", observed=True)[\\\"defaulted\\\"].mean()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(14, 5))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"band_default.plot(kind=\\\"bar\\\", ax=axes[0], color=\\\"coral\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[0].set_title(\\\"Default Rate by Credit Score Band\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[0].set_ylabel(\\\"Default Rate\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[0].tick_params(axis=\\\"x\\\", rotation=30)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Correlation heatmap\\n\",\n",
    "    \"numeric = [\\\"credit_score\\\", \\\"income\\\", \\\"loan_amount\\\", \\\"dti_ratio\\\", \\\"age\\\", \\\"employment_years\\\", \\\"defaulted\\\"]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"sns.heatmap(df[numeric].corr(), annot=True, fmt=\\\".2f\\\", cmap=\\\"coolwarm\\\", center=0, ax=axes[1])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[1].set_title(\\\"Correlation Matrix\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.tight_layout()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.show()\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c008\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# Default rate by loan purpose\\n\",\n",
    "    \"purpose_default = df.groupby(\\\"loan_purpose\\\")[\\\"defaulted\\\"].agg([\\\"mean\\\", \\\"count\\\"]).sort_values(\\\"mean\\\", ascending=False)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"=== Default Rate by Loan Purpose ===\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"purpose_default\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c009\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# Statistical test\\n\",\n",
    "    \"defaulters = df[df[\\\"defaulted\\\"]==1][\\\"credit_score\\\"]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"non_defaulters = df[df[\\\"defaulted\\\"]==0][\\\"credit_score\\\"]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"stat, p = stats.mannwhitneyu(non_defaulters, defaulters, alternative=\\\"greater\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Non-defaulter avg credit score: {non_defaulters.mean():.0f}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Defaulter avg credit score: {defaulters.mean():.0f}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Mann-Whitney U: p={p:.2e} → {'Significant' if p<0.05 else 'Not significant'}\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m003\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Key Findings\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. **Credit score is the strongest single predictor** of default — lower scores show dramatically higher default rates.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. **DTI ratio is the second most important factor** — high debt relative to income increases risk.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. **Employment tenure provides a modest protective effect** — stable employment reduces default probability.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. **Loan-to-income ratio matters** — borrowers who borrow large amounts relative to income are riskier.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Limitations\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Synthetic data; real credit data has more nuanced features.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- No payment history or behavioral data.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- No macroeconomic conditions modeled.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Recommendations / Next Steps\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. Build a credit scoring model using the identified drivers.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. Set DTI ratio limits for loan approval.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. Implement risk-based pricing tied to credit score bands.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. Monitor portfolio default rate trends over time.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Common Mistakes\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. Using credit score alone without considering DTI and employment stability.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. Not validating models across different economic periods.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. Ignoring fairness and bias in credit decisions.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. Not distinguishing between strategic default and inability to pay.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Mini Challenge / Exercises\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. Build a logistic regression model to predict default.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. Create risk segments (Low/Medium/High) based on multiple factors.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. Calculate expected loss (default probability × loan amount) by segment.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. Design a credit policy with approval rules based on this analysis.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Final Summary / Key Takeaways\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **Credit score and DTI ratio are the strongest default predictors.**\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **Risk-based segmentation enables better pricing and approval decisions.**\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **EDA should precede any modeling to understand feature behavior and relationships.**\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  }\n",
    " ],\n",
